                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>At the meeting of the Political Affairs Committee of the Allied High Commission
                    on April 21, the question of tripartite action on the question of all-German
                    elections was, at the request of the British and <pb facs="0649" n="633"
                        xml:id="pg_633"/> French, referred to the High Commissioners. The High
                    Commissioners considered the question at a private meeting following the 26th
                    session of the Council on April 27, and adopted a statement calling upon their
                    governments to “consider the propriety of an approach to the Soviet authorities
                    for the holding of free all-German elections.” (Telegrams 3415, April 15, from
                    Frankfort and 192, April 27, from Bonn, neither printed, 762A.00/4–2150 and
                    396.1–LO/4–2750.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
